    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "Going on endless pilgrimages, the world died, exhausted by so much bathing!")), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "Despite Kab\u012Br\u2019s disdain for K\u0101sh\u012B and for organized religion, his followers soon generated a sectarian movement called the Kab\u012Br Panth and established a major center right in K\u0101sh\u012B. The center has lent its name to an entire sector of the city, now called Kab\u012Br Chaur\u0101.")), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "One who bathes in Manik\u0101rnik\u0101 bathes in all t\u012Brthas. One who sees Vishveshvara makes all pilgrimages. One should always see Vishveshvara and always bathe in Manik\u0101rnik\u0101.")), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "To an outsider and, indeed, to most Hindus, the city may appear as a disordered, crowded jungle of temples. But to those Hindus whose vision is recorded in the m\u0101h\u0101tmyas of K\u0101sh\u012B\u2014those who see the city as a mandala\u2014these temples are all part of an ordered whole, a structured universe with its own divine functionaries and its own constellations of deities. And their vision is embodied in the sacred geography of the city.")), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
